VN. Harish, a highly competent singer from Chennai and a disciple of Akhila Siva and Vairamangalam Lakshminarayanan presented a pleasing  vocal concert for the monthly Sabha Swarajhari of Vijayawada at Sri Sivaramakrishna Kshetram. As an able violinist, Harish has performed successfully in many prestigious sabhas all over the country and received accolades.The concert started withKambhoji Ata tala varnamand this was followed by a superb rendition ofRanidi radu  -  Ponidi poduof Thyagaraja inragam Manirangu, aragathat sounds similar toSriragambut is a tricky one to elaboratethe distinct flavour. TheswarasHarish rendered were also crisp and lively.Hiranmayeem(Lalita),Neevalla Gunadoshammemi(kafi) andParasakthi(Saveri) preceded the main itemSukhi YevvaroinKanada. With his deep and resonant voice Harish brought out a charming portrait of theragaand sang thekeertanawith appropriatebhava. Finekalpana swarasadorned thekeertana.B.V.Durgabhavani on the violin, Mandapaka Nagalakshmi (mridangam) and I. Anjaneya Sastry (ghatam) gave Harish fine support. Bhavani's versions ofBegadaandKanadawere melodious. Nagalakshmi and Anjaneya Sastry gave an excellent rhythmic treat at the end of theKanada keertana. The closing part of Harish's concert consisted ofKanakasaila vihariniinPunnagavarali, Samayamideof Patnam inBehagand Lalgudi's popularthillanainMohanakalyani.In memoriamA stalwart of the stage and an experience organiser and director of many social dramas, Polavarapu Suryaprakasa Rao passed away recently creating a void in the world of theatre.Suryaprakasa Rao was actively associated with Andhra Nataka Kala Parishat for more than five decades and his services to the stage were unforgettable.P. SURYA RAOBottom Template Starts
